-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                Important
A program, also known as software, is a set of instructions that a computer follows to perform a task.
Before you start coding always think through the design of what it is that you're coding.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Given a problem, you can solve that problem using an algorithm, which is a high-level step-by-step
guide to complete a task. Generally, it involves 5 steps:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 1 - Declare known values & unknown values
Step 2 - Initialize known values
Step 3 - Get values for the unknown
Step 4 – Implement your code logic
Step 5 – Output the program
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                Practice Program 1
                                               Topics: Encapsulation
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Write a class Person. Create a private fields called profession & schoolName and create its getter and setter methods.
Create a Student and in the main method crate object of the Person class to set the profession as student and schoolName
as SprintQA and get the newly set value on the console. The output of your program should be:

I am a student and I study at SprintQA
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                Practice Program 2
                                               Topics: Wrapper class
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Write a program to declare short, integer, double, character, and boolean primitive variables. Initialize these
variables with your desired values. Use the autoboxing feature of Java to convert these variable into objects.
Once done, write print statements to convert them back to primitive types using the unboxing feature of Java.
The output of your program should be:

short value: 5
integer value: 6
double value: 5.005
character value: S
boolean value: true
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                Practice Program 3
                                               Topics: Wrapper class
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Write a program to declare byte, long, float, and character objects. Initialize these
variables with null and print them on the console.
The output of your program should be:

Byte value: null
Long value: null
Float value: null
Character value: null
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
